During a press briefing aboard Air Force One, White House Deputy Press Secretary Sarah Sanders provided updates on President Trump's upcoming executive order on Buy American and Hire American. She also mentioned that the Paris climate meeting has been rescheduled due to scheduling conflicts and that the Prime Minister of Italy will visit on Thursday. Sanders answered questions about the delay of the Paris climate meeting, the President's feelings about the Paris agreement, the situation in Turkey, and the executive order. She emphasized that the President's priority is to keep Americans safe and that he will work with other countries to achieve this goal. Sanders also addressed questions about the President's phone call with the Turkish President and the hiring practices at Mar-a-Lago. She promised to provide more information on these topics later.